t-align:left;\" |'''Total'''\n|157 353\n|100.00\n|170 733\n|100.00\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Azerbaijanis]]\n|148 862\n|94.60\n|163 092\n|95.52\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Lezgins]]\n|7 469\n|4.75\n|7 152\n|4.19\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Russians]]\n|231\n|0.15\n|121\n|0.07\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Turkish people]]\n|45\n|0.03\n|26\n|0.02\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Kurds]]\n|47\n|0.03\n|26\n|0.02\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Avars (Caucasus)|Avars]]\n|15\n|0.01\n|14\n|0.01\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Tatars]]\n|61\n|0.04\n|10\n|0.01\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Ukrainians]]\n|128\n|0.08\n|6\n|0.00\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Georgians]]\n|13\n|0.01\n|...\n|...\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |Others\n|475\n|0.30\n|286\n|0.17 \n|}\n\nAlternative according to the data of [[Lezgins]] ~ 40,000.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://books.google.com/?id=360iAQAAIAAJ&q=%D0%9B%D0%B5%D0%B7%D0%B3%D0%B8%D0%BD |title = \u0423\u0433\u0440\u043e\u0437\u044b \u043d\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0431\u0435\u0437\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0421\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u043e\u043c \u041a\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0435: \u044d\u0442\u043d\u043e\u043a\u043e\u043d\u0444\u0435\u0441\u0441\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0430\u0441\u043f\u0435\u043a\u0442|year = 2004}}</ref>\n\n== Climate ==\nThe annual sum of sunny hours is 2350 hours. Approximately 40 percents of sunny hours are observed in summer. The climate in Shaki is influenced by various air masses, cyclones and anticyclones, and local winds. Arctic and mild air masses enter Shaki with causing the temperature rise in the winter. Mountain winds form local winds in Sheki in the summer. It is because of a contrast in pressure between the mountain and the valley. The cold winds are moderated by the Great Caucasus from the north. Thus, the temperature in Sheki is 0.5 C in January. The average annual temperature is 12 C in Sheki. The average temperature ranges from 20 to 25 C in June and August.\n\nIn Sheki solid winds (over 15m / s) are hardly ever seen, with as 10\u201312 days a solid wind. Less than 1 meter per second the speed of the wind in Sheki is often observed. The average sum of rainfall is 730&nbsp;mm. 50% of it falls in May, June, September and October. In Kish village the least precipitation is in August (35&nbsp;mm), January (29&nbsp;mm) and February (36&nbsp;mm), 775&nbsp;mm, over 1000&nbsp;mm rainfall in Khan Lowland. Floods, storm, and hail are characteristic for the mountain and the fields encompassing Sheki and its urban places.\n\nThe flood event is observed frequently. The Kish Waterway basin is located in the western portion of the city and it is considered one of the most powerful flood areas in the world. In the place called Guruchay were collected sand, stone, and mud from the mountains for a long time and its middle part is higher than the city Dodo settlement. The atmosphere events such as the storm and the hail have a great deal of effect here. High relief, strong heat in the summer and high evaporation are the essential reasons of hail in Shaki.\n\nThe elevation of 500\u2013850 m above sea level, the mountain woodlands encompassing it prevents the city from overheating. The city is secured from floods by mountain woodlands. It makes the view of the city even more beautiful. The mountainous grassland, brown mountain woodlands, meadow-forest, gray brown soils cover the city. Oak, peanuts, hornbeam trees are spacious in the woodlands. The animal world is rich.\n\nThe main streams of the city are Kish and Gurcana rivers. Kish is the right arm of Eyrichay, it is 33&nbsp;km long, and the basin area is 265 km<sup>2</sup>. It starts at 2900 meters above the southern slope of the main Caucasian Range. It is one of the most flooded rivers of Transcaucasia. The upper axis is called Damarchin.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://anl.az/down/meqale/movqe/2011/iyul/189502.htm|title=Sheki district|website=The National Library of Azerbaijan}}</ref>\n\n== Notable persons ==\n[[Mirza Fatali Akhundov]] - writer, public figure\n\n[[Bakhtiyar Vahabzadeh]] - poet\n\n[[Molla C\u00fcm\u0259]] - poet\n\n[[Ahmadiyya Jabrayilov]] - World War II participant, partisan\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Iki arvadli]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Shaki Rayon}}\n*{{official website|http://sheki-ih.gov.az}}\n\n{{Shaki Rayon}}\n\n{{coord|41|06|N|47|00|E|region:AZ_source:kolossus-simplewiki|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Districts of Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:Shaki District| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Shekay District}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}}\n{{short description|District of Azerbaijan}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name = Shaki<br>\u015e\u0259ki\n| type = [[Administrative divisions of Azerbaijan|Rayon]]\n| image_skyline = Looking North from Sheki (3846239867).jpg\n| image_caption =Looking north from the Sheki Rayon\n| image_map = Azerbaijan-Shaki rayonu.png\n| map_caption = Map of Azerbaijan showing Shaki Rayon (in red)\n| subdivision_type = Country\n| subdivision_name = [[Azerbaijan]]\n| established_date = 8 August 1930\n| established_title = Established\n| population_as_of = 2018\n| population_total = 184,500\n| population_footnotes=<ref name=\"stats15\">{{cite web|url=http://www.stat.gov.az/source/demoqraphy/en/001_19-20en.xls|title= Population by sex, economic and administrative regions, urban settlements of the Republic of Azerbaijan at the beginning of the 2015 |publisher= The State Statistical Committee of the Azerbaijan Republic|accessdate=9 August 2015 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150820103456/http://www.stat.gov.az/source/demoqraphy/en/001_19-20en.xls | archive-date = 20 August 2015}}</ref>\n| area_total_km2 =2,430\n| population_density_km2 = 76\n| area_code_type = Telephone code\n| area_code = 0117\n| postal_code_type = Postal code\n| postal_code = 5500\n| seat_type = Capital\n| seat = [[Sheki, Azerbaijan|Sheki]]\n| language=Azerbaijan , Lezgi\n| leader_title            = Chief Executive\n| leader_name             =Elxan Zabir o\u011flu Usubov \n| leader_party= [[New Azerbaijan Party]]\n| website = {{url|http://sheki-ih.gov.az}}\n}}\n\n'''Shaki''' or '''\u015eeki''' ({{lang-az|\u015e\u0259ki rayonu}}) is a [[Administrative divisions of Azerbaijan|rayon]] of [[Azerbaijan]]. Its administrative capital is [[Sheki, Azerbaijan|Sheki]]. It is located on the southern slope of the [[Greater Caucasus]]. Sheki borders by [[Dagestan]] in the north-east. Yevlakh-Balakan railway and highways pass through Shaki.\n\n== History ==\nSheki is one of the oldest cities in [[Azerbaijan]]. In medieval sources, its name is called Shaki, Shaki, Shakki, and etc. The city of Sheki was called \"Nuxa\" for a long time. One of the oldest authors, [[Ptolemy]], noted that there was a settlement called \"Niga\" among Albanian cities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://files.preslib.az/projects/azerbaijan/eng/gl2.pdf|title=TERRITORIAL AND ADMINISTRATIVE UNITS - District of Shaki}}</ref>\n\nAfter the [[Ilkhanate]] collapsed, along with the Shirvanshahs state Shaki gained autonomy and the Orlat nobility came to power, in the first half of the XIV century. In 1551 Shaki's autonomy ended by Shah Tahmasib and Sheki joined the Safavid Empire. In 1743, Shaki Khanate was established.\n\nIn 1772 because of the overthrow of the Kish River, the historical city of Shaki was completely destroyed, some parts of the city's population had been harassed, some people had moved to other places, and some had settled in the present place of the city.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sheki.mctgov.az/az/view/363/1/Seki|title=History of Sheki|website=Sheki Regional Cultural Department|language=az}}</ref>\n\n=== Historical monuments ===\nThere are [[Palace of Shaki Khans]] (inscribed in [[UNESCO]]\u2019s [[World Heritage Site|World Heritage List]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1549/|title=Historic Centre of Sheki with the Khan's Palace|last=Centre|first=UNESCO World Heritage|website=UNESCO World Heritage Centre|language=en|access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref>) dating back to the XVIII century, Tower fortress, minaret of Gileyli mosque, Lower Caravanserai belonging to the XVIII-XIX centuries, Upper Caravanserai, Aghvanlar baths dating back to the 19th century in the city. \"Gavur\" fortress belonging to VI century, Gudula fortress of the Middle Ages, Aghcagala Mosque in Aydinbulag village,  Kish temple belonging to the medieval era near the Kish village, and [[Galarsan-Gorarsan|\"G\u0259l\u0259rs\u0259n g\u00f6r\u0259rs\u0259n]]\" fortress (in English ''\"See if you come\")'' dating back to the 15th century are preserved in the district.\n\n==Demographics==\n\nShaki has 65 settlements, with the majority of residents living in the cities  (66,900) and a minority in villages (32,600).<ref name=\"stats15\"/> The official languages are [[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]]. \n\nAccording to the [[State Statistics Committee (Azerbaijan)|State Statistics Committee]], as of 2018, the population of city was 185,400 persons, which increased by 26,700 persons (about 16.8 percent) from 158,700 persons in 2000.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.stat.gov.az/source/demoqraphy/?lang=en|title=Political division, population size and structure: Population by towns and regions of the Republic of Azerbaijan|website=The State Statistical Committee of the Republic of Azerbaijan|language=en|access-date=2018-12-18}}</ref> 92,700 of total population are men, 92,700 are women.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stat.gov.az/source/demoqraphy/?lang=en|title=Political division, population size and structure: Population by sex, towns and regions, urban settlements of the Republic of Azerbaijan at the beginning of the 2018|website=The State Statistical Committee of the Republic of Azerbaijan|language=en|access-date=2018-12-18}}</ref> More than 25.1 percent of the population (about 46,600 persons) consists of young people and teenagers aged 14\u201329.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stat.gov.az/source/demoqraphy/?lang=en|title=Political division, population size and structure: Population at age 14-29 by towns and regions of the Republic of Azerbaijan at the beginning of the 2018|website=The State Statistical Committee of the Republic of Azerbaijan|language=en|access-date=2018-12-18}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+'''The population of the district by the year (at the beginning of the year, thousand persons)''' <ref name=\":0\" />\n!Territory\n!2000\n!2001\n!2002\n!2003\n!2004\n!2005\n!2006\n!2007\n!2008\n!2009\n!2010\n!2011\n!2012\n!2013\n!2014\n!2015\n!2016\n!2017\n!2018\n|-\n|Shaki town \n|158,7\n|159,9\n|160,9\n|162,1\n|163,2\n|164,6\n|165,8\n|167,3\n|169,0\n|170,4\n|171,8\n|173,5\n|175,7\n|177,5\n|179,1\n|181,0\n|182,7\n|184,2\n|185,4\n|-\n|urban population\n|63,5\n|63,6\n|63,7\n|63,8\n|64,0\n|64,3\n|64,6\n|64,7\n|65,1\n|65,3\n|65,6\n|65,9\n|66,1\n|66,4\n|66,6\n|66,9\n|67,3\n|67,4\n|67,6\n|-\n|rural population\n|95,2\n|96,3\n|97,2\n|98,3\n|99,2\n|100,3\n|101,2\n|102,6\n|103,9\n|105,1\n|106,2\n|107,6\n|109,6\n|111,1\n|112,5\n|114,1\n|115,4\n|116,8\n|117,8\n|}\n\n==Economy==\n\nThere are 1 city, 2 settlements, 68 villages, and 31 rural executive offices, 1 city municipality and 39 rural municipalities in the district. There are 343 managerial and organizational departments, 17 bank branches, 14 hotels, 1 communication and 1 post office. The largest enterprise according to the number of employees is Shaki-Ipek OJSC.\n\nShaki is part of the [[Shaki-Zaqatala]] economic region. The Shaki region, one of the largest agricultural and industrial districts of the Republic, has a total area of 2.43 thousand km<sup>2</sup> and a population of 184,172. At present 29 industrial enterprises operate in the region, of which 21 are small enterprises.\n\n=== Population ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: right;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |'''Ethnic group'''\n! colspan=\"2\" |1999<ref name=\"Ethnic composition of Azerbaijan by 1999 census\">[http://pop-stat.mashke.org Population statistics of Eastern Europe]: [http://pop-stat.mashke.org/azerbaijan-ethnic1999.htm Ethnic composition of Azerbaijan by 1999 census]</ref>\n! colspan=\"2\" |2009<ref name=\"Ethnic composition of Azerbaijan by 2009 census\">[http://pop-stat.mashke.org Population statistics of Eastern Europe]: [http://pop-stat.mashke.org/azerbaijan-ethnic2009.htm Ethnic composition of Azerbaijan by 2009 census]</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#e0e0e0;\"\n!Number\n!%\n!Number\n!%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |'''Total'''\n|157 353\n|100.00\n|170 733\n|100.00\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Azerbaijanis]]\n|148 862\n|94.60\n|163 092\n|95.52\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Lezgins]]\n|7 469\n|4.75\n|7 152\n|4.19\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Russians]]\n|231\n|0.15\n|121\n|0.07\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Turkish people]]\n|45\n|0.03\n|26\n|0.02\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Kurds]]\n|47\n|0.03\n|26\n|0.02\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Avars (Caucasus)|Avars]]\n|15\n|0.01\n|14\n|0.01\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Tatars]]\n|61\n|0.04\n|10\n|0.01\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Ukrainians]]\n|128\n|0.08\n|6\n|0.00\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Georgians]]\n|13\n|0.01\n|...\n|...\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |Others\n|475\n|0.30\n|286\n|0.17 \n|}\n\nAlternative according to the data of [[Lezgins]] ~ 40,000<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://books.google.com/?id=360iAQAAIAAJ&q=%D0%9B%D0%B5%D0%B7%D0%B3%D0%B8%D0%BD |title = \u0423\u0433\u0440\u043e\u0437\u044b \u043d\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0431\u0435\u0437\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0421\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u043e\u043c \u041a\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0435: \u044d\u0442\u043d\u043e\u043a\u043e\u043d\u0444\u0435\u0441\u0441\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0430\u0441\u043f\u0435\u043a\u0442|year = 2004}}</ref>.\n\n== Climate ==\nThe annual sum of sunny hours is 2350 hours. Approximately 40 percents of sunny hours are observed in summer. The climate in Shaki is influenced by various air masses, cyclones and anticyclones, and local winds. Arctic and mild air masses enter Shaki with causing the temperature rise in the winter. Mountain winds form local winds in Sheki in the summer. It is because of a contrast in pressure between the mountain and the valley. The cold winds are moderated by the Great Caucasus from the north. Thus, the temperature in Sheki is 0.5 C in January. The average annual temperature is 12 C in Sheki. The average temperature ranges from 20 to 25 C in June and August.\n\nIn Sheki solid winds (over 15m / s) are hardly ever seen, with as 10\u201312 days a solid wind. Less than 1 meter per second the speed of the wind in Sheki is often observed. The average sum of rainfall is 730&nbsp;mm. 50% of it falls in May, June, September and October. In Kish village the least precipitation is in August (35&nbsp;mm), January (29&nbsp;mm) and February (36&nbsp;mm), 775&nbsp;mm, over 1000&nbsp;mm rainfall in Khan Lowland. Floods, storm, and hail are characteristic for the mountain and the fields encompassing Sheki and its urban places.\n\nThe flood event is observed frequently. The Kish Waterway basin is located in the western portion of the city and it is considered one of the most powerful flood areas in the world. In the place called Guruchay were collected sand, stone, and mud from the mountains for a long time and its middle part is higher than the city Dodo settlement. The atmosphere events such as the storm and the hail have a great deal of effect here. High relief, strong heat in the summer and high evaporation are the essential reasons of hail in Shaki.\n\nThe elevation of 500\u2013850 m above sea level, the mountain woodlands encompassing it prevents the city from overheating. The city is secured from floods by mountain woodlands. It makes the view of the city even more beautiful. The mountainous grassland, brown mountain woodlands, meadow-forest, gray brown soils cover the city. Oak, peanuts, hornbeam trees are spacious in the woodlands. The animal world is rich.\n\nThe main streams of the city are Kish and Gurcana rivers. Kish is the right arm of Eyrichay, it is 33&nbsp;km long, and the basin area is 265 km<sup>2</sup>. It starts at 2900 meters above the southern slope of the main Caucasian Range. It is one of the most flooded rivers of Transcaucasia. The upper axis is called Damarchin.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://anl.az/down/meqale/movqe/2011/iyul/189502.htm|title=Sheki district|website=The National Library of Azerbaijan}}</ref>\n\n== Notable persons ==\n[[Mirza Fatali Akhundov]] - writer, public figure\n\n[[Bakhtiyar Vahabzadeh]] - poet\n\n[[Molla C\u00fcm\u0259]] - poet\n\n[[Ahmadiyya Jabrayilov]] - World War II participant, partisan\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Iki arvadli]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Shaki Rayon}}\n*{{official website|http://sheki-ih.gov.az}}\n\n{{Shaki Rayon}}\n\n{{coord|41|06|N|47|00|E|region:AZ_source:kolossus-simplewiki|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Districts of Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:Shaki District| ]]\n", "name_user": "DannyS712", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixing the location of periods / full stops", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shaki_District"}
{"title_page": "William Chapman White", "text_new": "'''William Chapman White''' (February 20, 1903 \u2013 November 28, 1955) was a foreign correspondent in the 1930s who became a columnist for the ''[[New York Times]]'' and the [[New York Herald Tribune]]. He is known especially for his 1954 book, ''Adirondack Country''. His connection with the Adirondacks was through his marriage to Ruth Morris, daughter of the theatrical agent, William Morris, founder of the [[William Morris Agency]] who owned a \"cure camp\" on Lake Colby in [[Saranac Lake, New York]]. The Adirondack Research Room of the Saranac Lake Free Library is named for him.\n\n== Bibliography ==\nHis books include:\n*''These Russians'' (Scribner, 1931)\n*''Mouseknees'' (1939)<ref name=NYPL>{{cite web | url=https://digitalcollections.nypl.org/items/86556230-a611-0134-0eef-00505686a51c | title= (text) Mouseknees, (1939) |author=Digital Collections, The New York Public Library |accessdate=June 13, 2018 |publisher=The New York Public Library, Astor, Lennox, and Tilden Foundation}}</ref>\n*''Adirondack Country'' ({{ISBN|978-0-8156019-3-7}}) (1954)\n*''Just About Everything in the Adirondacks'' ({{ISBN|978-0-8156802-8-4}}) (1960)\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=W9Nd9Y3UGXYC&printsec=frontcover&dq=adirondack+country+william+chapman+white ''Adirondack Country'' (partial text)]\n* A sample of his work is found in [https://books.google.com/books?id=kHPHC1_2jDkC&pg=PA198&lpg=PA198&dq=William+Chapman+White&source=bl&ots=rRUJc4xQuC&sig=6cKpXRk_metV5IuSRHA2vJ0an0s&hl=en&ei=2-7YSbewJaXslQe87cTeDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10#PPA198,M1 ''The Tavern Lamps are Burning'', at Google Books]\n* More in Unz Org [http://www.unz.org/Author/WhiteWilliamChapman] Several articles about Russia and Germany.\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:White, William Chapman}}\n[[Category:1955 deaths]]\n[[Category:1903 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male writers]]\n", "text_old": "'''William Chapman White''' (February 20, 1903 \u2013 November 28, 1955) was a foreign correspondent in the 1930s who became a columnist for the ''[[New York Times]]'' and the [[New York Herald Tribune]]. He is known especially for his 1954 book, ''Adirondack Country''. His connection with the Adirondacks was through his marriage to Ruth Morris, daughter of the theatrical agent, William Morris, founder of the [[William Morris Agency]] who owned a \"cure camp\" on Lake Colby in [[Saranac Lake, New York]]. The Adirondack Research Room of the Saranac Lake Free Library is named for him.\n\n== Bibliography ==\nHis books include:\n*''These Russians'' (Scribner, 1931)\n*''Mouseknees'' (1939)<ref name=NYPL>{{cite web | url=https://digitalcollections.nypl.org/items/86556230-a611-0134-0eef-00505686a51c | title= (text) Mouseknees, (1939) |author=Digital Collections, The New York Public Library |accessdate=June 13, 2018 |publisher=The New York Public Library, Astor, Lennox, and Tilden Foundation}}</ref>\n*''Adirondack Country'' ({{ISBN|978-0-8156019-3-7}}) (1954)\n*''Just About Everything in the Adirondacks'' ({{ISBN|978-0-8156802-8-4}}) (1960)\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=W9Nd9Y3UGXYC&printsec=frontcover&dq=adirondack+country+william+chapman+white ''Adirondack Country'' (partial text)]\n* A sample of his work is found in [https://books.google.com/books?id=kHPHC1_2jDkC&pg=PA198&lpg=PA198&dq=William+Chapman+White&source=bl&ots=rRUJc4xQuC&sig=6cKpXRk_metV5IuSRHA2vJ0an0s&hl=en&ei=2-7YSbewJaXslQe87cTeDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10#PPA198,M1 ''The Tavern Lamps are Burning'', at Google Books]\n* More in Unz Org [http://www.unz.org/Author/WhiteWilliamChapman] Several articles about Russia and Germany.\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:White, William Chapman}}\n[[Category:1955 deaths]]\n[[Category:1903 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male writers]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Chapman_White"}
{"title_page": "Seth Putnam", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=June 2011}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Seth Putnam\n| image = Seth Putnam.jpg\n| image_size =\n| landscape  =\n| background = solo_singer \n| caption = Putnam in 2007\n| birth_name = Seth Edward Putnam\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1968|5|15|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Newton, Massachusetts|Newton]], [[Massachusetts]], United States\n| death_date = {{Death date and age|mf=yes|2011|06|11|1968|5|15}}\n| origin =\n| genre = {{flatlist|\n* [[Grindcore]]\n* [[thrash metal]]\n* [[hardcore punk]]\n}}\n| instrument = {{flatlist|\n* [[Singing|Vocals]]\n* [[guitar]]\n* [[Bass guitar|bass]]\n* [[Drum kit|drums]]\n}}\n| occupation = Musician\n| years_active = 1986\u20132011\n| associated_acts = [[Anal Cunt]]\n| label = {{flatlist|\n* Wicked Sick\n* Limited Appeal\n* [[Earache Records]]\n}}\n| website = \n}}\n\n'''Seth Edward Putnam''' (May 15, 1968 \u2013 June 11, 2011)<ref name=\"BMDead\">{{cite web |url=http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=159315 |title=Anal C**T Frontman Seth Putnam Dead At 43 |website=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |date=June 11, 2011 |accessdate=August 11, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110614032943/http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=159315 |archivedate=June 14, 2011}}</ref> was an American musician who was the founder, vocalist and occasional guitarist of [[grindcore]] band [[Anal Cunt]]. He was known for his high-pitched screamed vocals and lyrics that either shock, offend, or invoke [[black comedy|morbid humor]]. Throughout his career, Putnam was also involved in numerous side projects.\n\n==Biography==\n===Early years===\nPutnam was born on May 15, 1968, in [[Newton, Massachusetts]]<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/71292842 |title=Seth Edward Putnam |website=[[Find a Grave]] |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref> to father Edward R. Putnam and mother Barbara Ann Donohue. His parents are divorced. Seth was married to his first wife, Alison, from December 1998 through June 2001. He married Julie, his second wife, in 2008. In the mid-1980s, Putnam played bass in the [[thrash metal]] band [[Executioner (band)|Executioner]].\n\n===Personality===\nDespite his shock humor and turbulent lifestyle, Putnam was often described by fans and peers as a warm, intelligent, sensitive man. Putnam saw himself as a [[comedian]] and used music as an outlet.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.decibelmagazine.com/2011/06/28/seth-putnam-remembered/ |title=Seth Putnam Remembered |date=June 28, 2011 |first=Shawn |last=Macomber |magazine=[[Decibel (magazine)|Decibel]] |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn school, classmates who knew Putnam described him as intelligent and stern, but unmotivated, apathetic and often an underwhelming student. Putnam skipped a grade in school and became a very bright student, tutoring his classmates. In his own words, Putnam often blamed brutal fights with Catholic school nuns for helping to shape his cynical personality. When he reached high school after eighth grade, he had lost interest in excelling in education or academics, becoming more of a slacker and underachiever.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thegauntlet.com/article/467/20831/Seth-Putnam-from-Anal-Cunt-discusses-growing-up.html |title=Seth Putnam from Anal Cunt discusses growing up |date=January 5, 2011 |first=Jason |last=Fisher |website=The Gauntlet |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref> By the time he had graduated school, Putnam had left the Catholic religion in which he was raised. After graduation, Putnam showed no interest in attending college or university.\n\nThe 2019 grindcore documentary ''Slave to the Grind'' explores Putnam in detail, with his peers expressing the duality of his nature:<ref name=\"sttg\">{{Citation | title = Slave to the Grind | publisher = Death by Digital| year = 2019 | url = https://reelhouse.org/deathbydigital/slave-to-the-grind/slave-to-the-grind }}</ref> former bandmates Tim Morse and Scott Hull describe Putnam often being personable and relaxed, but Hull also notes that he'd often get arrested causing trouble on the street.<ref name=\"sttg\"/> [[Discordance Axis]] singer Jon Chang notes that he was really close to Putnam for years, but describes him as a \"really disturbed guy\" and a \"backstabbing piece of shit at the end of his life\". Chang also recounted an incident \nafter a show when Putnam introduced his mother to Chang, he remarked that they had met earlier when he pulled Putnam's mother out from the show's [[moshpit]], causing Putnam to become aggressive and threaten Chang, much to the confusion of everyone present.<ref name=\"sttg\"/> \nPutnam was also good friends with [[Pantera]] frontman, [[Phil Anselmo|Philip Anselmo]].\n\n===Drug overdose and coma===\nOn October 12, 2004 Putnam was hospitalized after ingesting a cocktail of [[crack-cocaine]], [[alcohol (drug)|alcohol]], [[heroin]], and two months' worth of [[Ambien]] sleeping pills.<ref name=\"coma\">{{cite news |url=http://www.bostonphoenix.com/boston/music/cellars/documents/05023497.asp |title=Coma chameleon - Seth Putnam's near-death experience |first=Carly |last=Carioli |newspaper=[[Boston Phoenix]] |date=October 12, 2004 |accessdate=August 5, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051217193005/http://www.bostonphoenix.com/boston/music/cellars/documents/05023497.asp |archivedate=December 17, 2005 |url-status=dead }}</ref> It has been reported that he spent the previous day contemplating suicide,<ref name=\"coma\" /> though exact circumstances surrounding the drug overdose are vague.\n\nAnal Cunt's 1997 album ''I Like It When You Die'' contained the track \"You're in a Coma\". Putnam's reaction to the resulting irony of being in a coma was published in the ''[[Boston Phoenix]]'': \"Actually, it turned out it was just as gay as the song I wrote nine years ago \u2013 being in a coma was just as fuckin' stupid as I wrote it was.\"<ref name=\"coma\" /> Anal Cunt kept performing the song during live shows after the coma, with Putnam sharing anecdotes with the audience before the song.{{cn|date=May 2019}}\n\n===Feud with Chris Barnes===\nThere was friction between Putnam and [[Six Feet Under (band)|Six Feet Under]] vocalist [[Chris Barnes (musician)|Chris Barnes]]. According to Putnam's defunct website, Putnam heckled Barnes during a Six Feet Under set, leading to an altercation between the two, ending with Six Feet Under's roadies ganging up on Putnam while Barnes fled to his tour bus and hid there. Putnam released the song \"[[It Just Gets Worse|Chris Barnes Is a Pussy]]\" as retaliation to the incident.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wickedsickrecords.com/SP_FAQs.htm |title=Seth Putnam Frequently Asked ?'s |website=Wicked Sick Records |date=April 16, 2003 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090330181724/http://www.wickedsickrecords.com/SP_FAQs.htm |archivedate=March 30, 2009 |accessdate=August 11, 2012 |url-status=live}}</ref> According to Putnam in an interview with Capital Chaos TV several years later, Six Feet Under went out of their way to avoid playing in the same city as Anal Cunt several years after the incident. Putnam stated \"I guess he (Chris Barnes) is still afraid of me\". Despite the feud, Putnam stated that \"[[Bringer of Blood|Murdered in the Basement]]\" was his favorite song by Six Feet Under.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/anal-cunt-s-seth-putnam-chris-barnes-is-a-pussy/ |title=Anal Cunt's Seth Putnam: 'Chris Barnes Is A Pussy' |website=Blabbermouth.net |date=November 4, 2003 |accessdate=August 11, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Death==\nOn June 11, 2011, Putnam died of a suspected [[heart attack]] at the age of 43.<ref name=\"BMDead\" /><ref>{{cite news |first=Rosie |last=Swash |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2011/jun/13/seth-putnam-dies-aged-43 |title=Seth Putnam, the 'GG Allin of grindcore', dies aged 43  |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London, UK |date=June 13, 2011 |accessdate=August 11, 2012}}</ref>\n\nPutnam's grave is located within Newton Cemetery in Newton, Massachusetts.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==Side projects and former bands==\n{{More citations needed section|date=September 2019}}\n\n====Angry Hate====\nThe idea of the band came up when Seth and Larry Lifeless (Kilslug vocalist) were drunk one night watching [[Jerry Springer]] and Larry said \"That guy looks like he should be in an old punk band called Angry Hate or something\". The first recording was in January ,1999, of Larry hammering a fence against some lady's garage which was put on at the end of the song, \"M.P.\" on the first release. That summer, they recorded four songs. all of them were old Sickness songs. \"Blinking Blue Lights\" was actually recorded by Kilslug, but never released. The other songs that were done originally by the Sickness never got released either. They made another E.P. called \"Bad Mood\" that had a certain amount of copies pressed but were never officially released. Seth and Lee Suniga (owner of Menace To Sobriety Records) sold them on eBay. Angry Hate performed two live shows in March and April 2002.\n\n====Satan's Warriors====\nSatan's Warriors started in February of 1986 after Seth and his friends made up a fake death metal fanzine with fake band names as a joke, Seth eventually admitted to doing it, in April of that year. There was an opening for a band to play live over the radio so Seth got a lineup together and made a four-song demo with him on drums and vocals and his cousin Drew on guitar. Their final show was on July of 1988. They were supposed to get back together in 2003 and re-record some songs written between 1986 and 1988. The lineup was supposed to be with Seth on guitar & vocals, Paulie Kraynak on second guitar, and John Gillis on drums.\n\n====Impaled Northern Moonforest====\nIn early 1997, Seth and Josh Martin came up with the idea of starting a joke black metal band and decided to record a demo, they didn't use actual drums because someone was sleeping in the room next to them so Josh played his acoustic guitar while Seth did vocals and percussion by slapping his leg and a mattress, they did a few shows and sold copies of their first demo, the titles on the demo are different from the ones on the 7\" vinyl release due to Seth and Josh losing their copies of the demo and forgetting the titles.\n\n====Shit Scum====\nShit Scum formed in 1988 after Seth saw an ad looking for musicians, Seth chose to call after seeing Cryptic Slaughter as the only influence because not many people in Boston were into that band. Seth eventually invited Fred Ordonez to see Satan's Warriors (which was their last show), Anal Cunt was also playing what was supposed to be their last show but Fred and his friends never showed up, so Seth did another show with Anal Cunt so Fred could see them, Shit Scum also did their first show on the same day. Seth was eventually invited to a studio to play bass on their first demo called \"Self Mutilation\", they later did a show in 1990, Seth and Fred (without Wayne who was their drummer) went to a studio that college rock bands mainly performed at. The engineer didn't like them and tried convincing them to quit, the record was eventually finished and they ended up owing the studio money so the studio kept the master reel. Anal Cunt did a tour in Germany and did some Shit Scum covers. Matthias Weigand (head of Ecocentric Records) liked the cover of the song \"Shit Scum\" and wanted to put out a 7\". Seth called the studio and asked about the reel, the guy on the phone said \"it's right here, pick it up whenever you want\", not knowing they owed money to the studio. Seth mixed all the songs and sent them to Ecocentric Records. Fred never had a cover for the record so Matthias made one up. The record was eventually called \"Manson Is Jesus\". Fred wanted the record to be called, \"I Wish this Record Could Punch You in the Face\", and have a fist on the cover. Shit Scum had already broken up by the time the album was released.\n\n====Full Blown A.I.D.S.====\nFull Blown A.I.D.S. started in 1997 while he was jamming with his friend and cousin. In 1998 he wrote some songs and recorded a demo of \"No One Cares\" with Nate Linehan on drums. In 2002 he moved to Texas for a while but eventually moved back to Boston. In 2003 the band went into the studio and recorded some songs and mixed them in a day. They eventually put out two E.P's and put out a compilation CD in 2008<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/2062039-Full-Blown-AIDS|title=Full Blown AIDS|last=|first=|date=|website=Discogs|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref> with both E.P's and the song \"Throwing Cars At People On Coke With Thor\".\n\n====Death's Head Quartet====\nThe Death's Head Quartet was a Jazz/Noise improv. band that featured Seth on bass and vocals, Chris Joyce on guitar, Robert Williams on drums, and Jim Hobbs on saxophone.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wickedsickrecords.com/SP_FAQs.htm#What%20are%20ALL%20the%20bands%20that%20Seth%20been%20involved%20with%20(including%20guest%20appearances)|title=SP FAQ's|website=www.wickedsickrecords.com|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref> Their first release was called \"Live on the Joint\" which was a radio broadcast from November 1, 2001. Their second release was recorded on April 9, 2001 and wasn't released until 2003.\n\n====Cuntsaw====\nCuntsaw started in 1989 with Seth on vocals and guitar and Tim Morse on drums. They usually practiced after Anal Cunt shows. They did one demo called \"Concerned\" and did one show at Brandeis University with Fred Ordonez on second guitar. They eventually broke up. The Anal Cunt Song \"Foreplay With A Tree Shredder\" was originally a Cuntsaw song that had a different title.\n\n====You're Fired====\nYou're Fired started in 2002. Within two months they had a nine-song demo recorded which eventually became the Warning E.P and was released in 2002. After Seth passed away, they made an E.P. called \"The End\" with Paulie Kraynak on guitar. Most of the riffs were written by Seth and the album was also recorded with Seth's Gibson SG and Marshall amplifier that were also used on the Warning E.P. \"The End\" was released in 2012 on vinyl and it also can be purchased on BandCamp along with the Warning E.P.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yourefiredboston.bandcamp.com/|title=The End (E.P.), by YOU'RE FIRED|website=YOU'RE FIRED|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref>\n\n====Pantera====\nIn 1996, Putnam did guest vocals on [[Pantera]]'s [[The Great Southern Trendkill]] for their songs,\"The Great Southern Trendkill\", \"War Nerve\", \"13 Steps to Nowhere\", and \"Suicide Note Pt. II\".\n\n====Adolf Satan====\nAdolf Satan started in 2002 after Upsidedown Cross broke up. Seth played drums for the band for a brief period of time. He eventually quit and Nate Linehan joined. They recorded a demo in 2003 and eventually made a self-titled studio album. They recorded another demo in 2006 before breaking up two years later.\n\n*[[Upsidedown Cross (band)|Upsidedown Cross]] (note: Although Putnam is credited playing guitar on their split with Sloth, the album was actually recorded years before he joined the band)\n*[[Executioner (band)|Executioner]]\n*[[Post Mortem (Boston Band)|Post Mortem]]\n*[[Siege (band)|Siege]]\n\n====P.O.D.D.A. (Pile Of Drunks & Drug Addicts)====\nNot much is known about this band but they had only one recording session in 2007 which eventually surfaced onto YouTube, the band had Seth on vocals, [https://www.discogs.com/artist/2659376-Dejan-Podobnik Dejan Podobnik](Patareni, Millions of Dead Cops...) on drums and Chomi on guitar. Mickey Offender from D.R.I., Offenders,  was supposed to lay a bass track but it never happened.(rip)\n\n====Sirhan Sirhan====\nThis band started in December of 1990 and Seth and Tim Morse were trying to think of a christmas gift for Mike Mahan who recently moved to Indiana, they recorded a demo and got a band picture in a $2 photo booth. They sent it to Mike who eventually lost his copy, the demo was released as a split album with Cuntsaw.\n\n====Insult====\nInsult started in 1992 and decided to record an album in 1997, it was going horribly for them so they got Seth to come in and produce their album, the album was called \"I Wanna Be A Burn Victim\", Seth eventually became their bass player and did a west coast tour with them in 1998 as well as a live show over the radio which was released on a split with Anal Cunt, he quit in 1999.\n\n====Person Killer====\nPerson Killer was a one man project Seth started around 1995, he made a demo and sent it to Earache Records along with a t-shirt, a pin, and a letter that didn't reveal the sender's name. It was planned to be released on a two LP set called \"The Worst Of Seth Putnam\" but it hasn't been released.\n\n===Vaginal Jesus===\nRumors circulated as to whether or not Putnam was a member of Vaginal Jesus, originally stating that he was just \"friends\" with the band. However, he later retracted this claim and publicly admitted to being a member.<ref>Resistance magazine // issue no. 25, Winter 2005/2006</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180623033415/http://www.racrecords.com/shop/magazines/resistance-magazine-issue-25-spring-2007/|title=Resistance Magazine Issue #25 Winter 2005 / 2006 \u2013 R.A.C. Records|date=23 June 2018|website=web.archive.org}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.inm.acousticblackmetal.com/ Impaled Northern Moonforest]\n* [http://www.inm.acousticblackmetal.com/impaled_northern_moonforest/index.html previous Impaled Northern Moonforest site]\n* [http://wickedsickrecords.com/SP_FAQs.htm#What%20are%20ALL%20the%20bands%20that%20Seth%20been%20involved%20with%20(including%20guest%20appearances)]\n* [http://www.wickedsickrecords.com/bands.html]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ku7b-YCQW_A]\n{{Anal Cunt}}\n{{Siege}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Putnam, Seth}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:2011 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:American heavy metal singers]]\n[[Category:American punk rock singers]]\n[[Category:American heavy metal guitarists]]\n[[Category:Place of death missing]]\n[[Category:American male singers]]\n[[Category:American male guitarists]]\n[[Category:American male bass guitarists]]\n[[Category:American multi-instrumentalists]]\n[[Category:Grindcore]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Boston]]\n[[Category:Former Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:20th-century male singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=June 2011}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Seth Putnam\n| image = Seth Putnam.jpg\n| image_size =\n| landscape  =\n| background = solo_singer \n| caption = Putnam in 2007\n| birth_name = Seth Edward Putnam\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1968|5|15|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Newton, Massachusetts|Newton]], [[Massachusetts]], United States\n| death_date = {{Death date and age|mf=yes|2011|06|11|1968|5|15}}\n| origin =\n| genre = {{flatlist|\n* [[Grindcore]]\n* [[thrash metal]]\n* [[hardcore punk]]\n}}\n| instrument = {{flatlist|\n* [[Singing|Vocals]]\n* [[guitar]]\n* [[Bass guitar|bass]]\n* [[Drum kit|drums]]\n}}\n| occupation = Musician\n| years_active = 1986\u20132011\n| associated_acts = [[Anal Cunt]]\n| label = {{flatlist|\n* Wicked Sick\n* Limited Appeal\n* [[Earache Records]]\n}}\n| website = \n}}\n\n'''Seth Edward Putnam''' (May 15, 1968 \u2013 June 11, 2011)<ref name=\"BMDead\">{{cite web |url=http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=159315 |title=Anal C**T Frontman Seth Putnam Dead At 43 |website=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |date=June 11, 2011 |accessdate=August 11, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110614032943/http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=159315 |archivedate=June 14, 2011}}</ref> was an American musician who was the founder, vocalist and occasional guitarist of [[grindcore]] band [[Anal Cunt]]. He was known for his high-pitched screamed vocals and lyrics that either shock, offend, or invoke [[black comedy|morbid humor]]. Throughout his career, Putnam was also involved in numerous side projects.\n\n==Biography==\n===Early years===\nPutnam was born on May 15, 1968, in [[Newton, Massachusetts]]<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/71292842 |title=Seth Edward Putnam |website=[[Find a Grave]] |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref> to father Edward R. Putnam and mother Barbara Ann Donohue. His parents are divorced. Seth was married to his first wife, Alison, from December 1998 through June 2001. He married Julie, his second wife, in 2008. In the mid-1980s, Putnam played bass in the [[thrash metal]] band [[Executioner (band)|Executioner]].\n\n===Personality===\nDespite his shock humor and turbulent lifestyle, Putnam was often described by fans and peers as a warm, intelligent, sensitive man. Putnam saw himself as a [[comedian]] and used music as an outlet.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.decibelmagazine.com/2011/06/28/seth-putnam-remembered/ |title=Seth Putnam Remembered |date=June 28, 2011 |first=Shawn |last=Macomber |magazine=[[Decibel (magazine)|Decibel]] |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn school, classmates who knew Putnam described him as intelligent and stern, but unmotivated, apathetic and often an underwhelming student. Putnam skipped a grade in school and became a very bright student, tutoring his classmates. In his own words, Putnam often blamed brutal fights with Catholic school nuns for helping to shape his cynical personality. When he reached high school after eighth grade, he had lost interest in excelling in education or academics, becoming more of a slacker and underachiever.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thegauntlet.com/article/467/20831/Seth-Putnam-from-Anal-Cunt-discusses-growing-up.html |title=Seth Putnam from Anal Cunt discusses growing up |date=January 5, 2011 |first=Jason |last=Fisher |website=The Gauntlet |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref> By the time he had graduated school, Putnam had left the Catholic religion in which he was raised. After graduation, Putnam showed no interest in attending college or university.\n\nThe 2019 grindcore documentary ''Slave to the Grind'' explores Putnam in detail, with his peers expressing the duality of his nature:<ref name=\"sttg\">{{Citation | title = Slave to the Grind | publisher = Death by Digital| year = 2019 | url = https://reelhouse.org/deathbydigital/slave-to-the-grind/slave-to-the-grind }}</ref> former bandmates Tim Morse and Scott Hull describe Putnam often being personable and relaxed, but Hull also notes that he'd often get arrested causing trouble on the street.<ref name=\"sttg\"/> [[Discordance Axis]] singer Jon Chang notes that he was really close to Putnam for years, but describes him as a \"really disturbed guy\" and a \"backstabbing piece of shit at the end of his life\". Chang also recounted an incident \nafter a show when Putnam introduced his mother to Chang, he remarked that they had met earlier when he pulled Putnam's mother out from the show's [[moshpit]], causing Putnam to become aggressive and threaten Chang, much to the confusion of everyone present.<ref name=\"sttg\"/> \nPutnam was also good friends with [[Pantera]] frontman, [[Phil Anselmo|Philip Anselmo]].\n\n===Drug overdose and coma===\nOn October 12, 2004 Putnam was hospitalized after ingesting a cocktail of [[crack-cocaine]], [[alcohol (drug)|alcohol]], [[heroin]], and two months' worth of [[Ambien]] sleeping pills.<ref name=\"coma\">{{cite news |url=http://www.bostonphoenix.com/boston/music/cellars/documents/05023497.asp |title=Coma chameleon - Seth Putnam's near-death experience |first=Carly |last=Carioli |newspaper=[[Boston Phoenix]] |date=October 12, 2004 |accessdate=August 5, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051217193005/http://www.bostonphoenix.com/boston/music/cellars/documents/05023497.asp |archivedate=December 17, 2005 |url-status=dead }}</ref> It has been reported that he spent the previous day contemplating suicide,<ref name=\"coma\" /> though exact circumstances surrounding the drug overdose are vague.\n\nAnal Cunt's 1997 album ''I Like It When You Die'' contained the track \"You're in a Coma\". Putnam's reaction to the resulting irony of being in a coma was published in the ''[[Boston Phoenix]]'': \"Actually, it turned out it was just as gay as the song I wrote nine years ago \u2013 being in a coma was just as fuckin' stupid as I wrote it was.\"<ref name=\"coma\" /> Anal Cunt kept performing the song during live shows after the coma, with Putnam sharing anecdotes with the audience before the song.{{cn|date=May 2019}}\n\n===Feud with Chris Barnes===\nThere was friction between Putnam and [[Six Feet Under (band)|Six Feet Under]] vocalist [[Chris Barnes (musician)|Chris Barnes]]. According to Putnam's defunct website, Putnam heckled Barnes during a Six Feet Under set, leading to an altercation between the two, ending with Six Feet Under's roadies ganging up on Putnam while Barnes fled to his tour bus and hid there. Putnam released the song \"[[It Just Gets Worse|Chris Barnes Is a Pussy]]\" as retaliation to the incident.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wickedsickrecords.com/SP_FAQs.htm |title=Seth Putnam Frequently Asked ?'s |website=Wicked Sick Records |date=April 16, 2003 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090330181724/http://www.wickedsickrecords.com/SP_FAQs.htm |archivedate=March 30, 2009 |accessdate=August 11, 2012 |url-status=live}}</ref> According to Putnam in an interview with Capital Chaos TV several years later, Six Feet Under went out of their way to avoid playing in the same city as Anal Cunt several years after the incident. Putnam stated \"I guess he (Chris Barnes) is still afraid of me\". Despite the feud, Putnam stated that \"[[Bringer of Blood|Murdered in the Basement]]\" was his favorite song by Six Feet Under.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/anal-cunt-s-seth-putnam-chris-barnes-is-a-pussy/ |title=Anal Cunt's Seth Putnam: 'Chris Barnes Is A Pussy' |website=Blabbermouth.net |date=November 4, 2003 |accessdate=August 11, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Death==\nOn June 11, 2011, Putnam died of a suspected [[heart attack]] at the age of 43.<ref name=\"BMDead\" /><ref>{{cite news |first=Rosie |last=Swash |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2011/jun/13/seth-putnam-dies-aged-43 |title=Seth Putnam, the 'GG Allin of grindcore', dies aged 43  |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London, UK |date=June 13, 2011 |accessdate=August 11, 2012}}</ref>\n\nPutnam's grave is located within Newton Cemetery in Newton, Massachusetts.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==Side projects and former bands==\n{{More citations needed section|date=September 2019}}\n\n====Angry Hate====\nThe idea of the band came up when Seth and Larry Lifeless (Kilslug vocalist) were drunk one night watching [[Jerry Springer]] and Larry said \"That guy looks like he should be in an old punk band called Angry Hate or something\". The first recording was in January ,1999, of Larry hammering a fence against some lady's garage which was put on at the end of the song, \"M.P.\" on the first release. That summer, they recorded four songs. all of them were old Sickness songs. \"Blinking Blue Lights\" was actually recorded by Kilslug, but never released. The other songs that were done originally by the Sickness never got released either. They made another E.P. called \"Bad Mood\" that had a certain amount of copies pressed but were never officially released. Seth and Lee Suniga (owner of Menace To Sobriety Records) sold them on eBay. Angry Hate performed two live shows in March and April 2002.\n\n====Satan's Warriors====\nSatan's Warriors started in February of 1986 after Seth and his friends made up a fake death metal fanzine with fake band names as a joke, Seth eventually admitted to doing it, in April of that year. There was an opening for a band to play live over the radio so Seth got a lineup together and made a four-song demo with him on drums and vocals and his cousin Drew on guitar. Their final show was on July of 1988. They were supposed to get back together in 2003 and re-record some songs written between 1986 and 1988. The lineup was supposed to be with Seth on guitar & vocals, Paulie Kraynak on second guitar, and John Gillis on drums.\n\n====Impaled Northern Moonforest====\nIn early 1997, Seth and Josh Martin came up with the idea of starting a joke black metal band and decided to record a demo, they didn't use actual drums because someone was sleeping in the room next to them so Josh played his acoustic guitar while Seth did vocals and percussion by slapping his leg and a mattress, they did a few shows and sold copies of their first demo, the titles on the demo are different from the ones on the 7\" vinyl release due to Seth and Josh losing their copies of the demo and forgetting the titles.\n\n====Shit Scum====\nShit Scum formed in 1988 after Seth saw an ad looking for musicians, Seth chose to call after seeing Cryptic Slaughter as the only influence because not many people in Boston were into that band. Seth eventually invited Fred Ordonez to see Satan's Warriors (which was their last show), Anal Cunt was also playing what was supposed to be their last show but Fred and his friends never showed up, so Seth did another show with Anal Cunt so Fred could see them, Shit Scum also did their first show on the same day. Seth was eventually invited to a studio to play bass on their first demo called \"Self Mutilation\", they later did a show in 1990, Seth and Fred (without Wayne who was their drummer) went to a studio that college rock bands mainly performed at. The engineer didn't like them and tried convincing them to quit, the record was eventually finished and they ended up owing the studio money so the studio kept the master reel. Anal Cunt did a tour in Germany and did some Shit Scum covers. Matthias Weigand (head of Ecocentric Records) liked the cover of the song \"Shit Scum\" and wanted to put out a 7\". Seth called the studio and asked about the reel, the guy on the phone said \"it's right here, pick it up whenever you want\", not knowing they owed money to the studio. Seth mixed all the songs and sent them to Ecocentric Records. Fred never had a cover for the record so Matthias made one up. The record was eventually called \"Manson Is Jesus\". Fred wanted the record to be called, \"I Wish this Record Could Punch You in the Face\", and have a fist on the cover. Shit Scum had already broken up by the time the album was released.\n\n====Full Blown A.I.D.S.====\nFull Blown A.I.D.S. started in 1997 while he was jamming with his friend and cousin. In 1998 he wrote some songs and recorded a demo of \"No One Cares\" with Nate Linehan on drums. In 2002 he moved to Texas for a while but eventually moved back to Boston. In 2003 the band went into the studio and recorded some songs and mixed them in a day. They eventually put out two E.P's and put out a compilation CD in 2008<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/2062039-Full-Blown-AIDS|title=Full Blown AIDS|last=|first=|date=|website=Discogs|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref> with both E.P's and the song \"Throwing Cars At People On Coke With Thor\".\n\n====Death's Head Quartet====\nThe Death's Head Quartet was a Jazz/Noise improv. band that featured Seth on bass and vocals, Chris Joyce on guitar, Robert Williams on drums, and Jim Hobbs on saxophone<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wickedsickrecords.com/SP_FAQs.htm#What%20are%20ALL%20the%20bands%20that%20Seth%20been%20involved%20with%20(including%20guest%20appearances)|title=SP FAQ's|website=www.wickedsickrecords.com|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref>. Their first release was called \"Live on the Joint\" which was a radio broadcast from November 1, 2001. Their second release was recorded on April 9, 2001 and wasn't released until 2003.\n\n====Cuntsaw====\nCuntsaw started in 1989 with Seth on vocals and guitar and Tim Morse on drums. They usually practiced after Anal Cunt shows. They did one demo called \"Concerned\" and did one show at Brandeis University with Fred Ordonez on second guitar. They eventually broke up. The Anal Cunt Song \"Foreplay With A Tree Shredder\" was originally a Cuntsaw song that had a different title.\n\n====You're Fired====\nYou're Fired started in 2002. Within two months they had a nine-song demo recorded which eventually became the Warning E.P and was released in 2002. After Seth passed away, they made an E.P. called \"The End\" with Paulie Kraynak on guitar. Most of the riffs were written by Seth and the album was also recorded with Seth's Gibson SG and Marshall amplifier that were also used on the Warning E.P. \"The End\" was released in 2012 on vinyl and it also can be purchased on BandCamp along with the Warning E.P.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yourefiredboston.bandcamp.com/|title=The End (E.P.), by YOU'RE FIRED|website=YOU'RE FIRED|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref>\n\n====Pantera====\nIn 1996, Putnam did guest vocals on [[Pantera]]'s [[The Great Southern Trendkill]] for their songs,\"The Great Southern Trendkill\", \"War Nerve\", \"13 Steps to Nowhere\", and \"Suicide Note Pt. II\".\n\n====Adolf Satan====\nAdolf Satan started in 2002 after Upsidedown Cross broke up. Seth played drums for the band for a brief period of time. He eventually quit and Nate Linehan joined. They recorded a demo in 2003 and eventually made a self-titled studio album. They recorded another demo in 2006 before breaking up two years later.\n\n*[[Upsidedown Cross (band)|Upsidedown Cross]] (note: Although Putnam is credited playing guitar on their split with Sloth, the album was actually recorded years before he joined the band)\n*[[Executioner (band)|Executioner]]\n*[[Post Mortem (Boston Band)|Post Mortem]]\n*[[Siege (band)|Siege]]\n\n====P.O.D.D.A. (Pile Of Drunks & Drug Addicts)====\nNot much is known about this band but they had only one recording session in 2007 which eventually surfaced onto YouTube, the band had Seth on vocals, [https://www.discogs.com/artist/2659376-Dejan-Podobnik Dejan Podobnik](Patareni, Millions of Dead Cops...) on drums and Chomi on guitar. Mickey Offender from D.R.I., Offenders,  was supposed to lay a bass track but it never happened.(rip)\n\n====Sirhan Sirhan====\nThis band started in December of 1990 and Seth and Tim Morse were trying to think of a christmas gift for Mike Mahan who recently moved to Indiana, they recorded a demo and got a band picture in a $2 photo booth. They sent it to Mike who eventually lost his copy, the demo was released as a split album with Cuntsaw.\n\n====Insult====\nInsult started in 1992 and decided to record an album in 1997, it was going horribly for them so they got Seth to come in and produce their album, the album was called \"I Wanna Be A Burn Victim\", Seth eventually became their bass player and did a west coast tour with them in 1998 as well as a live show over the radio which was released on a split with Anal Cunt, he quit in 1999.\n\n====Person Killer====\nPerson Killer was a one man project Seth started around 1995, he made a demo and sent it to Earache Records along with a t-shirt, a pin, and a letter that didn't reveal the sender's name. It was planned to be released on a two LP set called \"The Worst Of Seth Putnam\" but it hasn't been released.\n\n===Vaginal Jesus===\nRumors circulated as to whether or not Putnam was a member of Vaginal Jesus, originally stating that he was just \"friends\" with the band. However, he later retracted this claim and publicly admitted to being a member.<ref>Resistance magazine // issue no. 25, Winter 2005/2006</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180623033415/http://www.racrecords.com/shop/magazines/resistance-magazine-issue-25-spring-2007/|title=Resistance Magazine Issue #25 Winter 2005 / 2006 \u2013 R.A.C. Records|date=23 June 2018|website=web.archive.org}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.inm.acousticblackmetal.com/ Impaled Northern Moonforest]\n* [http://www.inm.acousticblackmetal.com/impaled_northern_moonforest/index.html previous Impaled Northern Moonforest site]\n* [http://wickedsickrecords.com/SP_FAQs.htm#What%20are%20ALL%20the%20bands%20that%20Seth%20been%20involved%20with%20(including%20guest%20appearances)]\n* [http://www.wickedsickrecords.com/bands.html]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ku7b-YCQW_A]\n{{Anal Cunt}}\n{{Siege}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Putnam, Seth}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:2011 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:American heavy metal singers]]\n[[Category:American punk rock singers]]\n[[Category:American heavy metal guitarists]]\n[[Category:Place of death missing]]\n[[Category:American male singers]]\n[[Category:American male guitarists]]\n[[Category:American male bass guitarists]]\n[[Category:American multi-instrumentalists]]\n[[Category:Grindcore]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Boston]]\n[[Category:Former Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:20th-century male singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "name_user": "DannyS712", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixing the location of periods / full stops", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seth_Putnam"}
{"title_page": "Service set (802.11 network)", "text_new": "[[File:SSID_ESS.svg|thumb|An example of a service set called \"WiFi Wikipedia\" consisting of two Basic Service Sets. Notebook_My is able to automatically [[roaming|roam]] between the two BSSs, without the user having to explicitly connect to the second network.]]\nIn [[IEEE 802.11]] [[wireless LAN|wireless local area network]]ing standards (including [[Wi-Fi]]), a '''service set''' (also known as '''extended service set''' or '''ESS''') is a group of wireless network devices which are identified by the same '''SSID''' ('''service set identifier'''). SSIDs serve as \"network names\" and are typically [[natural language]] labels. A service set forms a logical network -- that is operating with the same level 2 networking parameters -- they are on the same [[Logical link control|logical network segment]] (e.g., IP subnet or VLAN).\n\n'''Basic service sets''' ('''BSS''') are a subgroup of devices within a service set which are additionally also operating with the same physical layer [[medium access control|medium access]] characteristics (i.e. radio frequency, modulation scheme, security settings etc.) such that they are wirelessly networked. Devices within basic service sets are identified by '''BSSIDs''' ('''basic service set identifiers'''), which are 48-bit labels that conform to [[MAC-48]] conventions. While devices may have multiple BSSIDs, usually each BSSID is associated with at most one basic service set at a time.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.juniper.net/documentation/en_US/junos-space-apps/network-director2.0/topics/concept/wireless-ssid-bssid-essid.html#jd0e46|title=Understanding the Network Terms SSID, BSSID, and ESSID - Technical Documentation - Support - Juniper Networks|website=www.juniper.net}}</ref> There are two classes of basic service sets: those that are formed by an [[infrastructure mode]] redistribution point (access points or mesh nodes), and those that are formed by independent [[Station (networking)|stations]] in a peer-to-peer [[wireless ad hoc network|ad hoc topology]] (an '''Independent Basic Service Set''' or  '''IBSS'''.)\n\nA basic service set should not to be confused with the coverage area of an access point, known as the 'basic service area' (BSA).{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 3.15, p. 5}}\n\n==Basic service sets (BSSs){{anchor|BSS|IBSS|BSSID}}==\n===Infrastructure mode===\nAn [[infrastructure mode]] wireless network basic service set (BSS) consists of one redistribution point {{mdash}} typically an [[wireless access point|access point]] (WAP or AP) {{mdash}} together with one or more \"client\" stations<!-- in the standard, an AP is also a STA, so don't abbreviate --> that are associated with (i.e. connected to) that redistribution point.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 3.16, p. 6}} The operating parameters of the infrastructure-BSS are defined by the redistribution point. Stations communicate only with the redistribution point that they are associated with, and all traffic within the infrastructure-BSS is routed through/bridged by that redistribution point.\n\nEach basic service set has its own unique identifier, a BSSID, which is a unique 48-bit identifier that follows [[MAC address]] conventions.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.1.3.3, p. 6}} An infrastructure-BSSID is usually non-configurable, in which case it is either preset during manufacture, or mathematically derived from a preset value such as a serial number, the MAC address of the LAN connection, etc. As with the MAC addresses used for Ethernet devices, infrastructure-BSSIDs are a combination of a 24-bit Organization Unique Identifier (OUI, the manufacturer's identity) and a 24-bit serial number. A BSSID with a value of all 1s is used to indicate the wildcard BSSID, usable only during probe requests or for communications that take place outside the context of a BSS.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.1.3.3.3, p. 65}}\n\n===Mesh basic service set===\nFrom the point of view of a wireless clients, [[IEEE 802.11s]] [[wireless mesh networks]] appear as a conventional infrastructure mode topology, and are centrally configured as such. The formation of the mesh's BSS, as well as wireless traffic management (including path selection and forwarding) is negotiated between the [[Node (networking)|nodes]] (redistribution points) of the mesh infrastructure. The mesh's BSS is distinct from the networks (which may also be wireless) used by a mesh's redistribution points to communicate with one another.\n\n===Ad hoc===\nIn contrast to the stations in an infrastructure-mode network, the stations in a [[wireless ad hoc network]] communicate directly with one another, i.e. without a dependence on a distribution point to relay traffic between them.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 5.6, p. 41}} In this form of peer-to-peer wireless networking, the peers form an independent basic service set (IBSS).{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 5.21, p. 25}} Some of the responsibilities of a distribution point {{mdash}} such as defining network parameters and other \"beaconing\" functions {{mdash}} are established by the first station in an ad-hoc network. But that station does not relay traffic between the other stations; instead, the peers communicate directly with one another. Like infrastructure-BSSs, independent-BSSs also have a 48-bit MAC address-like identifier. But unlike infrastructure-BSS identifiers, independent-BSSs identifiers are not necessarily unique: the individual/group bit of the address is always set to 0 (individual), the universal/local bit of the address is always set to 1 (local), and the remaining 46 bits are randomly generated.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.1.3.3.3, p. 65}}\n\n==Service set ID (WiFi){{anchor|SSID}}==\nThe SSID is broadcast by stations in beacon packets to announce the presence of a network.\n\nUnlike basic service set identifiers, SSIDs are usually customizable.{{sfn|Vasseur|Dunkels|2010|page=432}} These SSIDs can be zero to 32 [[octet (computing)|octet]]s (32 [[byte]]s) long,{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.3.2.1, p. 101}} and are, for convenience, usually in a [[natural language]], such as English. The 802.11 standards prior to the 2012 edition did not define any particular encoding/representation for SSIDs, which were expected to be treated and handled as an arbitrary sequence of 0{{ndash}}32 octets that are not limited to [[printable characters]]. The IEEE 802.11-2012 defines a tag that the SSID is [[UTF-8]] encoded and when interpreting could contain any non-[[ISO basic Latin alphabet|ISO basic Latin characters]] within it.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=IEEE|date=2012|title=Part 11: Wireless LAN Medium Access Control (MAC) and Physical Layer (PHY) Specifications Sponsored by the LAN/MAN Standards Committee|url=https://www.academia.edu/6564159|journal=IEEE 802.11-2012|language=en|volume=|pages=562|via=}}</ref> Wireless network stacks must still be prepared to handle arbitrary values in the SSID field.\n\nSince the contents of an SSID field are arbitrary, the 802.11 standard permits devices to advertise the presence of a wireless network with beacon packets in which the SSID field is set to null.{{sfn|Murty, et al|2008|p=75}}{{refn|group=\"n\"|<!-- off topic:-->To associate with a wireless network, a station must know the network's SSID. This information is either obtained from beacons broadcast by a base station (in which case a client can passively infer whether it is in range of that network), or {{mdash}} if no base station is advertising the SSID {{mdash}} a station must know the SSID beforehand by other means (e.g. from a previous configuration). When a client wishes to associate with a network, it sends the SSID in a probe request. An access point replies with a probe response if the SSID in a probe request is the wildcard SSID (SSID is zero-length) or matches a SSID that the access point supports{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 11.1.3.2.1, p. 422}} otherwise the access point does not respond to the probe request.}} A null SSID (the SSID element's 'length' field is set to zero{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.3.2.1, p. 101}}) is called a \"wildcard SSID\" in IEEE 802.11 standards documents,{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 11.1.3.2.1, p. 422}} and as a \"no broadcast SSID\" or \"hidden SSID\" in the context of beacon announcements,{{sfn|Murty, et al|2008|p=75}}{{sfn|Dornseif, et al|2002|p=2}} and can be used, for example, in enterprise and mesh networks to steer a client to a particular (e.g. less utilized) access point.{{sfn|Murty, et al|2008|p=75}} A station may also likewise transmit packets in which the SSID field is set to null; this prompts an associated access point to send the station a list of supported SSIDs.{{sfn|Lindqvist, et al|2009|pp=123f}} Once a device has associated with a basic service set, for efficiency, the SSID is not sent within packet headers; only BSSIDs are used for addressing.\n\n==Extended service sets (ESSs){{anchor|ESS|ESSID}}==\nFormally, there is no distinct ''ESSID'' in the 802.11 standards.{{sfn|Edney|2004|p=11}}{{sup|cf.{{nbsp}}}}{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=Definitions, \u00a7 3, p. 8}} In 802.11 standard documents, the logical network (ESS or independent-BSS) service set identifier is simply abbreviated ''SSID'',{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.3.2.1, p. 101}} irrespective of whether an SSID identifies an infrastructure-BSS's ESS, or the peer-to-peer network of an independent-BSS.\n\nAn extended service set (ESS) is a set of one or more infrastructure basic service sets on a common [[logical link control|logical network segment]] (i.e. same IP subnet and VLAN).{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 3.54, p. 8}} Key to the concept is that the participating basic service sets appear as a single network to the [[logical link control]] layer.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 3.54, p. 8}}{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 5.2.3.1, p. 26}} Thus, from the perspective of the logical link control layer, stations within an ESS may communicate with one another, and mobile stations may move transparently from one participating BSS to another (within the same ESS).{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 5.2.3.1, p. 26}} Extended service sets make possible distribution services such as centralized authentication and seamless roaming between infrastructure-BSSs. From the perspective of the link layer, all stations within an ESS are all on the same link, and transfer from one BSS to another is transparent to logical link control.{{sfn|Edney|2004|p=8}}\n\nThe basic service sets formed in [[wireless ad hoc network]]s are, by definition, independent from other BSSs, and an independent-BSS cannot therefore be part of an extended infrastructure.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 5.6, p. 40}} In that formal sense an independent-BSS has no extended service set. However, the network packets of both independent-BSSs and infrastructure-BSSs have a logical network service set identifier (described below), and the logical link control does not distinguish between the use of that field to name an ESS network, and the use of that field to name a peer-to-peer ad hoc network. The two are effectively indistinguishable at the logical link control layer level.{{sfn|Edney|2004|p=8}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=\"n\"}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Works cited===\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{citation\n|last=Dornseif|first=Maximillian\n|last2=Schumann|first2=Kay H.\n|last3=Klein|first3=Christian\n|title=Tats\u00e4chliche und rechtliche Risiken drahtloser Computernetzwerke\n|url=http://www.l13.de/itsec/whirl/200204-dud-wlan.pdf\n|journal=Datenschutz und Datensicherheit\n|volume=22|issue=4\n|year=2002\n|pages=1{{ndash}}5\n|ref={{harvid|Dornseif, et al|2002}}\n}}.\n* {{citation\n|last=Edney\n|first=Jon\n|year=2004\n|chapter=What is an ESS?\n|title=IEEE 802 LAN/MAN Standards Committee Meeting, July 2004\n|location=Piscataway, NJ\n|publisher=Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers\n|chapter-url=http://www.ieee802.org/21/doctree/2004_Meeting_Docs/2004-07_meeting_docs/21-04-0105-00-0000-what_ess.ppt\n}}.\n*{{citation\n|last=Lindqvist|first=Janne\n|last2=Aura|first2=Tuomas\n|last3=Danezis|first3=George\n|last4=Koponen|first4=Teemu\n|last5=Myllyniemi|first5=Annu\n|last6=M\u00e4ki|first6=Jussi\n|last7=Roe|first7=Michael\n|ref={{harvid|Lindqvist, et al|2009}}\n|chapter=Privacy-preserving 802.11 Access-point Discovery\n|pages=123{{ndash}}130\n|title=Proceedings of the Second ACM Conference on Wireless Network Security\n|series=WiSec '09\n|year=2009\n|location=New York|publisher=ACM\n|isbn=978-1-60558-460-7\n|doi=10.1145/1514274.1514293\n|citeseerx=10.1.1.206.4148\n}}.\n* {{citation\n|last=Murty|first=Rohan\n|last2=Padhye|first2=Jitendra\n|last3=Chandra|first3=Ranveer\n|last4=Wolman|first4=Alec\n|last5=Zill|first5=Brian\n|year=2008\n|chapter=Designing High Performance Enterprise Wi-Fi Networks\n|pages=73{{ndash}}88\n|chapter-url=http://static.usenix.org/event/nsdi08/tech/full_papers/murty/murty.pdf\n|title=Proceedings of the 5th USENIX Symposium on Networked Systems Design and Implementation\n|series=NSDI '08\n|editor-last=Crowcroft|editor-first=Jon\n|editor2-last=Dahlin|editor2-first=Mike\n|display-editors=etal\n|location=Berkeley, CA\n|publisher=USENIX Association\n|ref={{harvid|Murty, et al|2008}}\n}}.\n* {{citation\n|chapter-url=http://standards.ieee.org/getieee802/download/802.11p-2010.pdf\n|editor-last=Stacey|editor-first=Robert\n|editor2-last=Ecclesine|editor2-first=Peter\n|display-editors=etal\n|chapter={{null|Part 11: }}Wireless LAN Medium Access Control (MAC) and Physical Layer (PHY) Specifications, Amendment 6{{null|: Wireless Access in Vehicular Environments.}} (IEEE Std 802.11p-2010)\n|title=Local and Metropolitan Area Networks, Specific Requirements{{null|full title: 802.11p-2010 - IEEE Standard for Information technology--Telecommunications and information exchange between systems Local and metropolitan area networks--Specific requirements - Part 11: Wireless LAN Medium Access Control (MAC) and Physical Layer (PHY) Specifications, Amendment 6: Wireless Access in Vehicular Environments.}}\n|series=IEEE Standard for Information technology {{mdash}} Telecommunications and information exchange between systems\n|year=2010{{null|date=2010-07-15}}\n|location=Piscataway, NJ\n|publisher=Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers\n|isbn=978-0-7381-6324-6\n|ref={{harvid|IEEE Std 802.11p-2010}}\n}}.\n* {{citation\n|chapter-url=http://standards.ieee.org/getieee802/download/802.11-2007.pdf{{null|full title: 802.11-2007 - IEEE Standard for Information technology--Telecommunications and information exchange between systems Local and metropolitan area networks--Specific requirements - Part 11: Wireless LAN Medium Access Control (MAC) and Physical Layer (PHY) Specifications}}\n|editor-last=Cole|editor-first=Terry L.\n|editor2-last=Barber|editor2-first=Simon\n|chapter={{null|Part 11: }}Wireless LAN Medium Access Control (MAC) and Physical Layer (PHY) Specifications (IEEE Std 802.11-2007)\n|title=Local and Metropolitan Area Networks, Specific Requirements\n|series=IEEE Standard for Information technology{{mdash}} Telecommunications and information exchange between systems.\n|year=2007|{{null|date=2007-06-12}}\n|location=Piscataway, NJ\n|publisher=Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers\n|isbn=978-0-7381-5656-9\n|ref={{harvid|IEEE Std 802.11-2007}}\n}}.\n* {{citation\n|title=Interconnecting Smart Objects with IP: The Next Internet\n|first=Jean-Philippe\n|last=Vasseur\n|first2=Adam\n|last2=Dunkels\n|location=Burlington, MA\n|publisher=Morgan Kaufmann\n|isbn=978-0-12-375166-9\n|year=2010\n}}.\n{{refend}}\n\n[[Category:Wireless networking]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:SSID_ESS.svg|thumb|An example of a service set called \"WiFi Wikipedia\" consisting of two Basic Service Sets. Notebook_My is able to automatically [[roaming|roam]] between the two BSSs, without the user having to explicitly connect to the second network.]]\nIn [[IEEE 802.11]] [[wireless LAN|wireless local area network]]ing standards (including [[Wi-Fi]]), a '''service set''' (also known as '''extended service set''' or '''ESS''') is a group of wireless network devices which are identified by the same '''SSID''' ('''service set identifier'''). SSIDs serve as \"network names\" and are typically [[natural language]] labels. A service set forms a logical network -- that is operating with the same level 2 networking parameters -- they are on the same [[Logical link control|logical network segment]] (e.g., IP subnet or VLAN).\n\n'''Basic service sets''' ('''BSS''') are a subgroup of devices within a service set which are additionally also operating with the same physical layer [[medium access control|medium access]] characteristics (i.e. radio frequency, modulation scheme, security settings etc.) such that they are wirelessly networked. Devices within basic service sets are identified by '''BSSIDs''' ('''basic service set identifiers'''), which are 48-bit labels that conform to [[MAC-48]] conventions. While devices may have multiple BSSIDs, usually each BSSID is associated with at most one basic service set at a time.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.juniper.net/documentation/en_US/junos-space-apps/network-director2.0/topics/concept/wireless-ssid-bssid-essid.html#jd0e46|title=Understanding the Network Terms SSID, BSSID, and ESSID - Technical Documentation - Support - Juniper Networks|website=www.juniper.net}}</ref> There are two classes of basic service sets: those that are formed by an [[infrastructure mode]] redistribution point (access points or mesh nodes), and those that are formed by independent [[Station (networking)|stations]] in a peer-to-peer [[wireless ad hoc network|ad hoc topology]] (an '''Independent Basic Service Set''' or  '''IBSS'''.)\n\nA basic service set should not to be confused with the coverage area of an access point, known as the 'basic service area' (BSA).{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 3.15, p. 5}}\n\n==Basic service sets (BSSs){{anchor|BSS|IBSS|BSSID}}==\n===Infrastructure mode===\nAn [[infrastructure mode]] wireless network basic service set (BSS) consists of one redistribution point {{mdash}} typically an [[wireless access point|access point]] (WAP or AP) {{mdash}} together with one or more \"client\" stations<!-- in the standard, an AP is also a STA, so don't abbreviate --> that are associated with (i.e. connected to) that redistribution point.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 3.16, p. 6}} The operating parameters of the infrastructure-BSS are defined by the redistribution point. Stations communicate only with the redistribution point that they are associated with, and all traffic within the infrastructure-BSS is routed through/bridged by that redistribution point.\n\nEach basic service set has its own unique identifier, a BSSID, which is a unique 48-bit identifier that follows [[MAC address]] conventions.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.1.3.3, p. 6}} An infrastructure-BSSID is usually non-configurable, in which case it is either preset during manufacture, or mathematically derived from a preset value such as a serial number, the MAC address of the LAN connection, etc. As with the MAC addresses used for Ethernet devices, infrastructure-BSSIDs are a combination of a 24-bit Organization Unique Identifier (OUI, the manufacturer's identity) and a 24-bit serial number. A BSSID with a value of all 1s is used to indicate the wildcard BSSID, usable only during probe requests or for communications that take place outside the context of a BSS.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.1.3.3.3, p. 65}}\n\n===Mesh basic service set===\nFrom the point of view of a wireless clients, [[IEEE 802.11s]] [[wireless mesh networks]] appear as a conventional infrastructure mode topology, and are centrally configured as such. The formation of the mesh's BSS, as well as wireless traffic management (including path selection and forwarding) is negotiated between the [[Node (networking)|nodes]] (redistribution points) of the mesh infrastructure. The mesh's BSS is distinct from the networks (which may also be wireless) used by a mesh's redistribution points to communicate with one another.\n\n===Ad hoc===\nIn contrast to the stations in an infrastructure-mode network, the stations in a [[wireless ad hoc network]] communicate directly with one another, i.e. without a dependence on a distribution point to relay traffic between them.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 5.6, p. 41}} In this form of peer-to-peer wireless networking, the peers form an independent basic service set (IBSS).{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 5.21, p. 25}} Some of the responsibilities of a distribution point {{mdash}} such as defining network parameters and other \"beaconing\" functions {{mdash}} are established by the first station in an ad-hoc network. But that station does not relay traffic between the other stations; instead, the peers communicate directly with one another. Like infrastructure-BSSs, independent-BSSs also have a 48-bit MAC address-like identifier. But unlike infrastructure-BSS identifiers, independent-BSSs identifiers are not necessarily unique: the individual/group bit of the address is always set to 0 (individual), the universal/local bit of the address is always set to 1 (local), and the remaining 46 bits are randomly generated.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.1.3.3.3, p. 65}}\n\n==Service set ID (WiFi){{anchor|SSID}}==\nThe SSID is broadcast by stations in beacon packets to announce the presence of a network.\n\nUnlike basic service set identifiers, SSIDs are usually customizable.{{sfn|Vasseur|Dunkels|2010|page=432}} These SSIDs can be zero to 32 [[octet (computing)|octet]]s (32 [[byte]]s) long,{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.3.2.1, p. 101}} and are, for convenience, usually in a [[natural language]], such as English. The 802.11 standards prior to the 2012 edition did not define any particular encoding/representation for SSIDs, which were expected to be treated and handled as an arbitrary sequence of 0{{ndash}}32 octets that are not limited to [[printable characters]]. The IEEE 802.11-2012 defines a tag that the SSID is [[UTF-8]] encoded and when interpreting could contain any non-[[ISO basic Latin alphabet|ISO basic Latin characters]] within it<ref>{{Cite journal|last=IEEE|date=2012|title=Part 11: Wireless LAN Medium Access Control (MAC) and Physical Layer (PHY) Specifications Sponsored by the LAN/MAN Standards Committee|url=https://www.academia.edu/6564159|journal=IEEE 802.11-2012|language=en|volume=|pages=562|via=}}</ref>. Wireless network stacks must still be prepared to handle arbitrary values in the SSID field.\n\nSince the contents of an SSID field are arbitrary, the 802.11 standard permits devices to advertise the presence of a wireless network with beacon packets in which the SSID field is set to null.{{sfn|Murty, et al|2008|p=75}}{{refn|group=\"n\"|<!-- off topic:-->To associate with a wireless network, a station must know the network's SSID. This information is either obtained from beacons broadcast by a base station (in which case a client can passively infer whether it is in range of that network), or {{mdash}} if no base station is advertising the SSID {{mdash}} a station must know the SSID beforehand by other means (e.g. from a previous configuration). When a client wishes to associate with a network, it sends the SSID in a probe request. An access point replies with a probe response if the SSID in a probe request is the wildcard SSID (SSID is zero-length) or matches a SSID that the access point supports{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 11.1.3.2.1, p. 422}} otherwise the access point does not respond to the probe request.}} A null SSID (the SSID element's 'length' field is set to zero{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.3.2.1, p. 101}}) is called a \"wildcard SSID\" in IEEE 802.11 standards documents,{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 11.1.3.2.1, p. 422}} and as a \"no broadcast SSID\" or \"hidden SSID\" in the context of beacon announcements,{{sfn|Murty, et al|2008|p=75}}{{sfn|Dornseif, et al|2002|p=2}} and can be used, for example, in enterprise and mesh networks to steer a client to a particular (e.g. less utilized) access point.{{sfn|Murty, et al|2008|p=75}} A station may also likewise transmit packets in which the SSID field is set to null; this prompts an associated access point to send the station a list of supported SSIDs.{{sfn|Lindqvist, et al|2009|pp=123f}} Once a device has associated with a basic service set, for efficiency, the SSID is not sent within packet headers; only BSSIDs are used for addressing.\n\n==Extended service sets (ESSs){{anchor|ESS|ESSID}}==\nFormally, there is no distinct ''ESSID'' in the 802.11 standards.{{sfn|Edney|2004|p=11}}{{sup|cf.{{nbsp}}}}{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=Definitions, \u00a7 3, p. 8}} In 802.11 standard documents, the logical network (ESS or independent-BSS) service set identifier is simply abbreviated ''SSID'',{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 7.3.2.1, p. 101}} irrespective of whether an SSID identifies an infrastructure-BSS's ESS, or the peer-to-peer network of an independent-BSS.\n\nAn extended service set (ESS) is a set of one or more infrastructure basic service sets on a common [[logical link control|logical network segment]] (i.e. same IP subnet and VLAN).{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 3.54, p. 8}} Key to the concept is that the participating basic service sets appear as a single network to the [[logical link control]] layer.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 3.54, p. 8}}{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 5.2.3.1, p. 26}} Thus, from the perspective of the logical link control layer, stations within an ESS may communicate with one another, and mobile stations may move transparently from one participating BSS to another (within the same ESS).{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 5.2.3.1, p. 26}} Extended service sets make possible distribution services such as centralized authentication and seamless roaming between infrastructure-BSSs. From the perspective of the link layer, all stations within an ESS are all on the same link, and transfer from one BSS to another is transparent to logical link control.{{sfn|Edney|2004|p=8}}\n\nThe basic service sets formed in [[wireless ad hoc network]]s are, by definition, independent from other BSSs, and an independent-BSS cannot therefore be part of an extended infrastructure.{{sfn|IEEE Std 802.11-2007|loc=\u00a7 5.6, p. 40}} In that formal sense an independent-BSS has no extended service set. However, the network packets of both independent-BSSs and infrastructure-BSSs have a logical network service set identifier (described below), and the logical link control does not distinguish between the use of that field to name an ESS network, and the use of that field to name a peer-to-peer ad hoc network. The two are effectively indistinguishable at the logical link control layer level.{{sfn|Edney|2004|p=8}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=\"n\"}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Works cited===\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{citation\n|last=Dornseif|first=Maximillian\n|last2=Schumann|first2=Kay H.\n|last3=Klein|first3=Christian\n|title=Tats\u00e4chliche und rechtliche Risiken drahtloser Computernetzwerke\n|url=http://www.l13.de/itsec/whirl/200204-dud-wlan.pdf\n|journal=Datenschutz und Datensicherheit\n|volume=22|issue=4\n|year=2002\n|pages=1{{ndash}}5\n|ref={{harvid|Dornseif, et al|2002}}\n}}.\n* {{citation\n|last=Edney\n|first=Jon\n|year=2004\n|chapter=What is an ESS?\n|title=IEEE 802 LAN/MAN Standards Committee Meeting, July 2004\n|location=Piscataway, NJ\n|publisher=Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers\n|chapter-url=http://www.ieee802.org/21/doctree/2004_Meeting_Docs/2004-07_meeting_docs/21-04-0105-00-0000-what_ess.ppt\n}}.\n*{{citation\n|last=Lindqvist|first=Janne\n|last2=Aura|first2=Tuomas